()CertificationEntity kya hai?
CertificationEntity ek single reviewable object hai ek certification ke andar.
Ye ek unit of review represent karta hai, jaise ek user, account, role, ya application jiska access check ho raha hai.

Soch:-
Certification = pura campaign (100 users ka review)
CertificationEntity = ek user ya account ka review

Flow samajh:-
Certification Campaign
        ↓
Certification
        ↓
CertificationEntity (User Ravi)
        ↓
CertificationItem (Access 1, Access 2, Access 3)

🔹 2️⃣ CertificationEntity ka kaam:-
()Single review unit ko represent karna:-
Ek user/account ka access check karna.
()Identity / Account track karna:-
Kis user/account ka review ho raha hai.
()CertificationItems hold karna:-
Us entity ke sab access/permissions ka record.
()Reviewer assign karna:-
Kaun approve/reject karega.
()Status & Decision maintain karna:-
Pending, Approved, Revoked, Completed.
()Dates track karna:-
Kab created, kab completed.

🔹 3️⃣ CertificationEntity ke andar kya hota hai (Fields / Attributes):-
Field / Attribute	      Description
id:-------------------Unique ID of entity
name:-----------------Entity ka naam (user / account / role)
type:-----------------USER / ACCOUNT / ROLE / APPLICATION
identity:-------------Identity object (user info)
account:--------------Account object (agar account-based review)
items:----------------List of CertificationItem (access items under this entity)
reviewer:-------------Jo is entity ka review karega
status:---------------Pending / Approved / Revoked / Completed
decision:-------------Final decision (APPROVE/REVOKE)
createdDate:----------Entity kab create hua
completedDate:--------Kab complete hua

🔹 4️⃣ Example Code:-
CertificationEntity entity = new CertificationEntity();

// Basic info
entity.setId("CE101");
entity.setName("Ravi Kumar");
entity.setType("USER");

// Identity & Account
entity.setIdentity(userObject);
entity.setAccount(accountObject);

// Certification items
List<CertificationItem> items = new ArrayList<>();
items.add(item1);  // Role access
items.add(item2);  // App access
entity.setItems(items);

// Reviewer & status
entity.setReviewer("Manager Amit");
entity.setStatus("Pending");

// Dates
entity.setCreatedDate(new Date());

Output example:-
System.out.println(entity.getName());       // Ravi Kumar
System.out.println(entity.getType());       // USER
System.out.println(entity.getItems().size()); // 2
System.out.println(entity.getReviewer());   // Manager Amit
System.out.println(entity.getStatus());     // Pending

🔹 5️⃣ Real Life Example:-
Certification Campaign → “Quarterly Access Review”
Certification → “Managers Access Certification”
CertificationEntity → “User Ravi”
CertificationItem → Ravi ke access jaise SAP Role, HR App Access, Finance App Access

🔹 6️⃣ DB me store hota hai?
✅ Haan
CertificationEntity ko DB me child table ke form me store kiya jata hai
DB relation:-
Certification (parent) 
      ↓
CertificationEntity (child) 
      ↓
CertificationItem (child of entity)
Ye structure ensure karta hai ki har user/account ka access easily track ho aur report generate ho sake.

🔹 Owner / Responsible Role – Detailed Breakdown:-
Object	                  Owner/Responsible Ka Matlab	              Kaun Banata Hai/Assign Karta Hai	                                                Notes/Extra Detail
CertificationGroup:-------Group ka responsible banda:---------------Ye usually Admin / Compliance team assign karta hai:-------Jo group ke andar multiple certifications ko manage kare. Owner ensure karta hai ki group ke sab certifications track ho rahe hain.
CertificationManager:-----Certification ka manager/controller:------System ya Admin assign karta hai:---------------------------Manager decide karta hai certification flow, review assignments aur escalation rules.
CertificationDefinition:--Template/definition ka owner:-------------Admin/Compliance team:--------------------------------------Define karta hai kaun sa certification ka type hai, rules, frequency, reviewers, etc.
CertificationSchedule:----Schedule ka owner:------------------------Admin/Compliance team:--------------------------------------Ye decide karta hai kab certification run karega, duration, reminders, etc.
Certification:------------Campaign ka responsible banda:------------Admin/Compliance team/Certification creator:----------------Ye poora review campaign hai, multiple entities cover karta hai. Owner ensure karta hai campaign complete ho.
CertificationEntity:------Entity ke liye responsible reviewer:------Ye owner assign hota hai Certification ke flow me,usually entity ka Manager/App Owner:--------Ek entity ek user/account/role ko represent karta hai. Reviewer access approve/revoke karta hai.
CertificationItem:--------Access item ka decision maker:------------Ye CertificationEntity ka reviewer handle karta hai:--------Ek entity ke andar multiple items ho sakte hain. Reviewer approve/revoke ka decision deta hai.

